  "elapsed_s": 11.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So- in the same-- and on the same level also, Jewish were named Jewish councils were named, to take care of-- of the-- of the-- who should be in touch, who should communicate with the German authorities.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Because not every Jew can go and-- and talk to them.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It has to be a Jewish council who represent the Jewish community of Budapest.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And in this-- in this Jewish council, they call it-- the German called it Judenrat, in German.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And this is a Jewish council.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And the members of this council were these two professors, who-- who I was under their-- who know me from before.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was a Mr.-- the professor Pastor and Nemes and others like Stern was-- was some-- Rabbi Stern and all kind of rabbis who were chief-- who-- who conducted all kind of negotiations with Eichmann, who came to Hungary to talk about this Jewish problem, as they call it, resettlement of the Jews and do everything.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So-- so these rabbis, this-- this Jewish councils, the Judenrat, also put up posters asking the Jewish-- the Jewish residents of Budapest to conduct themselves in an orderly way, not to do trouble, and-- and everything should be-- should remain under control.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Otherwise, the Germans will see that we are-- we are not a good community.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we'll have troubles.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So-- and the [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And what happened to me next is that I-- yeah.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there was a poster about-- about putting up Jewish yellow-- Jewish stars.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Every Jew from this and this age should-- [INAUDIBLE] what size this yellow star should be and on what part of the body, of the jacket should be.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Everything has to be like it was according to the order.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
